obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (14118)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14118&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Central Silk Board Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 21 of 1970, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (14119)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of Union control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1953, s. 3, for section 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14119&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[2. Declaration as to expediency of Union control.--It is hereby declared that it is expedient in the`
  line `public interest that the Union should take under its control the silk industry.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (14120)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14120&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) Board means the Central Silk Board constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) "Central Silk-worm Seed Testing Laboratory" means the Central Seed Testing`
  line `Laboratory established or accredited under sub-section (1) of section 8G;`
  line
  line `(b) "charkha raw silk" means raw silk reeled from silk worm cocoons with the help of`
  line `any instrument not worked by power;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) "Committee" means the Central Silk-worm Seed Committee constituted under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(bb) "dealer" means a person who carries on the business of buying and selling, export or`
  line `import of silk-worm seed, cocoons, chawkie reared silk-worms and includes an agent of a dealer;`
  line
  line `(bc) "export" means taking out of India to a place outside India;]`
  line
  line `(c) "filature raw silk" means raw silk reeled from silk worm cocoons with the help of any`
  line `instrument worked by power;`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) "Hybrid Authorisation Committee" means the Hybrid Authorisation Committee`
  line `constituted under sub-section (1) of section 8D;`
  line
  line `(cb) import means bringing into India from a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(cc) "notified kind or variety" in relation to silk-worm seed means, any kind or variety`
  line `thereof notified under sub-section (1) of section 8C;]`
  line
  line `(d) "power" means any form of energy which is mechanically transmitted and is not generated by`
  line `human or animal agency, and includes electrical energy;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^2[(ea) "Registration Committee" means the Registration Committee constituted under subsection`
  line `(2) of section 8E;`
  line
  line `(eb) "regulation" means regulation made by the Committee under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ec) "silk-worm seed or seed" means all kinds of silk-worm seeds produced from the pure`
  line `silk-worm races including the hybrids produced from two or more pure races, silk-worm seed`
  line `cocoons of all kinds and moths thereof intended to be used or reared for the purpose of`
  line `production or for commercial exploitation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(i) "pure races" means silk-worm breed or variety maintained through reproductive`
  line `silk-worm seed with features true to the parents;`
  line
  line `(ii) "hybrids" means the seed produced involving two or more pure races or parental`
  line `races with the objective of exploiting heterosis or hybrid vigour;`
  line
  line `(ed) "Silk-worm Seed Analyst" means a Seed Analyst appointed or notified under sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 8G;`
  line
  line `(ee) "Silk-worm Seed Certification Agency" means the Silk-worm Seed Certification Agency`
  line `constituted or accredited under section 8F;`
  line
  line `(ef) "Silk-worm Seed Officer" means Seed Officer appointed or notified under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 8H;]`
  line
  line `(f) "spun silk" means silk yarn spun from pierced or spoilt cocoons, fluff from cocoons, pieces of`
  line `silk, coils, or other silk waste;`
  line
  line `(g) "Standing Committee" means the Standing Committee of the Board constituted under subsection`
  line `(2) of section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s.2 (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (14121)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14121&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of this Act, the`
  line `Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute for the purposes of this Act a`
  line `Board to be called the Central Silk Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a^2[Chairperson] to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `^3[(b) not more than three officials to be nominated by the Central Government, one of whom`
  line `shall be the head of the Silk Division in the Ministry of Textiles as the ^4[Vice-Chairperson] and one`
  line `shall be the Secretary of the Board, both being the officers not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India;]`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for any such official to depute in the prescribed circumstances`
  line `another official to attend any meeting of the Board on his behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) six persons to be elected by Parliament, four from the House of the People by the members of`
  line `the House of the People and two from the Council of States by the members of the Council of States;`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that a member of Parliament shall, upon ceasing to be a member of the House of the`
  line `People or as the case may be, the Council of States, cease to be a member of the Board.]`
  line
  line `(d)`
  line `^6[five persons] to be nominated by the Government of ^7[Karnataka], one of whom shall`
  line `represent the filature raw silk industry and two shall represent the rest of the sericulture industry;`
  line
  line `(e)`
  line `^8[one person] to be nominated by the Government of ^9[Tamil Nadu];`
  line
  line `(f) two persons to be nominated by the Governor of West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(g) one person to be nominated by each of the Governments of ^10[Andhra Pradesh], Assam, Bihar,`
  line `Chhattisgarh, ^11[Gujarat],`
  line `^12* * * , Madhya Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh and Uttaranchal;]`
  line
  line `(h) one person to be nominated by the Government of Jammu and Kashmir;`
  line
  line `(i) not more than three persons to be nominated by the Central Government to represent the`
  line `producers of raw silk and areas other than the States specified in clauses (d) to (g) inclusive;`
  line
  line `(j) eight persons to be nominated by the Central Government, of whom one shall represent the`
  line `spun-silk industry, one the silk throwing and twisting industry, one the silk weaving industry, one`
  line `labour; and two of them shall be experts in sericulture.]`
  line
  line `(4) The members of the Board shall receive from its funds such travelling and other allowances as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^13[(5) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the term of office of a member shall be such period,`
  line `not exceeding three years, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (5),--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government may terminate the appointment of the ^14[Chairperson]after giving`
  line `him notice for a period of not less than three months;`
  line
  line `(b) the ^14[Chairperson]may resign his office by giving notice in writing for a period of not`
  line `less than three months to the Central Government, and on such resignation being notified in the`
  line `Official Gazette by that Government, the ^14[Chairperson]shall be deemed to have vacated his`
  line office.]
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1953, s. 4, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 3, for "Chairman" (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Subs.by s. 4, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Vice-Chairman" (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A. O. (No. 3), 1956, for "four persons".`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by the Mysore State (Alteration of Name) (Adaption of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1974, for "Mysore"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-11-1973).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by the A. O. (No. 3), 1956, for "two persons".`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by the Madras State (Alteration of Name) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1970, for "Madras" (w.e.f.`
  line `14-1-1969).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by the A. O. (No. 3), 1956, for "Andhra".`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by the Bombay Reorganisation (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1961, for "Bombay" (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `12. The words "Madhya Bharat" omitted by the A. O. (No. 3), 1956.`
  line
  line `13. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 13 of 1982, s. 2.`
  line
  line `14.Subs. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 3, for "Chairman" (w.e.f.1-7-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (14122)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Disqualification for being nominated or appointed as a member of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14122&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A.Disqualification for being nominated or appointed as a member of Board.-- A person shall`
  line `be disqualified for being nominated or appointed or for continuing as a member, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is not a citizen of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(d) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his function as a`
  line member.]
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (14123)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of the Central Government in default of nominations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14123&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any Government other`
  line `than the Central Government fails to make any nomination which it is entitled to make under sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 4 within the time prescribed in that behalf, the Central Government may make the`
  line `nomination itself.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a member of the Board dies, resigns, is removed, ceases to reside in India, or becomes`
  line `incapable of acting, the authority or body entitled to nominate the member under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 4 may nominate a person to fill the vacancy; and where such nomination is not made within the`
  line `time prescribed in that behalf, the Central Government on its own initiative, may make the nomination`
  line itself.
  line
  line `(3) No act done by the Board shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (14124)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vice-Chairperson and Standing Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14124&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[The^2[Vice-Chairperson] shall] exercise such`
  line `of the powers and perform such of the duties of the ^3[Chairperson] as may be prescribed or as may be`
  line `delegated to him by the ^3[Chairperson].`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, in its discretion, constitute a Standing Committee for the purpose of exercising`
  line `such of its powers and performing such of its duties as may be delegated by it not being powers or duties`
  line `the delegation of which is prohibited by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Standing Committee shall consist of the ^3[Chairperson], the ^2[Vice-Chairperson], and five`
  line `others elected by the Board from among its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subsby the Act 42 of 2006, s. 6, for "The Central Government shall appoint from among the members of the Board, a ViceChairman`
  line `who shall"(w.e.f 1.7.2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, for"Vice-Chairman" (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3,ibid., for "Chairman" (w.e.f. 1-7-2007)`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (14125)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Secretary of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14125&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^2[The Secretary to the Board shall], under the control and direction of`
  line `the Board, exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to`
  line `him by the Board or the^1[Chairperson].`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3,ibid., for "Chairman" (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subsby s. 7, ibid., for "The Central Government shallappoint a Secretary to the Board who shall"(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (14126)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14126&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Board to promote the development of`
  line `the^1* * * silk industry by such measures as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the measures referred to therein`
  line `may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a)undertaking, assisting or encouraging scientific, technological and economic research;`
  line
  line `(b)devising means for improved methods of mulberry cultivation rearing, developing and`
  line `distributing healthy silkworm seeds,^2[reeling or, as the case may be, spinning of silkworm cocoons`
  line `and silk waste], improving the quality and production of raw silk, if necessary, by making it`
  line `compulsory for all raw silk to be marketed only after the same has been tested and graded in properly`
  line `equipped raw silk conditioning houses;`
  line
  line ^3******
  line
  line `(d) improving the marketing of raw silk;`
  line
  line `(e) the collection of statistics from such persons as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `^4[(f) carrying out any other duties which may be vested in the Board under rules made under this`
  line Act.]
  line
  line `(3) It shall also be the duty of the Board--`
  line
  line `^5[(a) to advise the Central Government on all matters relating to production, supply, distribution,`
  line `trade and commerce in silk-worm seed, the development of the silk industry and its products`
  line `including export and import;]`
  line
  line ^6*******
  line
  line `(c) to prepare and furnish such ^7*** reports relating to the ^8*** silk industry as may be required`
  line `by the Central Government from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "raw" omitted by Act 31 of 1953, s. 6(w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1970, s. 3, for "reeling of silkworm cocoons".`
  line
  line `3. Clause (c) omitted by s. 3, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 31 of 1953, s. 6 (w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
  line
  line `5. Subs by Act 42 of 2006, s. 8, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `6. Clause (b) omitted by Act 21 of 1970, s. 3.`
  line
  line `7. The word "other" omitted by s. 3, ibid.`
  line
  line `8.The word "raw" omitted by Act 31 of 1953, s. 6(w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (14127)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `Constitution of Central Silk-worm Seed Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14127&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Constitution of Central Silk-worm Seed Committee.--(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, constitute for the purposes of this Act, a Committee to be called the`
  line `Central Silk-worm Seed Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Vice-Chairperson of the Board who shall be the Chairperson of the Committee, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) (i) seven officials not below the rank of Deputy Secretary to the Government of India dealing`
  line `with sericulture from the States-members;`
  line
  line `(ii) two experts from the field of silk-worm seed development-members;`
  line
  line `(iii) five persons to represent the sericulture sector of whom three shall be the farmers and two the`
  line reelers-members;
  line
  line `to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst the members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the Director of the National Silk-worm Seed Organisation to be nominated by the Central`
  line `Government-member; and`
  line
  line `(d) Secretary of the Board who shall be the Secretary of the Committee, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee may associate with it, for such purposes and in such manner as it may deem fit,`
  line `any person whose assistance or advice it may consider necessary in complying with the provisions of this`
  line `Act, and a person so associated, shall have the right to take part in the proceedings of the Committee`
  line `relevant to the purposes for which he has been associated, but shall not have the right to vote and shall be`
  line `entitled to receive such allowances or fees as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A member nominated under sub-section (1) shall, unless his seat becomes vacant earlier by`
  line `resignation, death or otherwise, hold office for a period of three years from the date of his nomination and`
  line `shall be eligible for re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person nominated under sub-section (1) shall hold office only for so long as he holds`
  line `the appointment by virtue of which his nomination was made.`
  line
  line `(4) No act or proceeding of the Committee shall become invalid merely by reason of`
  line
  line `(i) any vacancy therein, or any defect in the constitution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any matter relating to the procedure of the Committee not affecting the merits of a case.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall provide to the Committee such other technical and other officers`
  line `and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of the functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) (a) The Committee shall meet at such time and place and shall observe such procedure in regard`
  line `to transaction of business at its meeting (including the quorum at meetings) as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(b) The Chairperson or in his absence any member chosen by the members present from amongst`
  line `themselves, shall preside at a meeting of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(c) All questions at a meeting of the Committee shall be decided by a majority of votes of the`
  line `members present and voting and in case of equality of votes, the Chairperson or in his absence, the`
  line `person presiding over the meeting shall have a second or casting vote.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (14128)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 11
  title `Powers and functions of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14128&sectionno=8B&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Powers and functions of Committee.--(1) The Committee shall be responsible for the`
  line `implementation of this Act by taking measures as specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the measures referred to therein`
  line `may provide for--`
  line
  line `(i) laying down of quality standards for kind or variety of silk-worm seed;`
  line
  line `(ii) authorisation of silk-worm races and hybrids for commercial exploitation;`
  line
  line `(iii) laying down of quality standards for production of silk-worm seeds;`
  line
  line `(iv) laying down the conditions and requirements that have to be met out by the persons desirous`
  line `of setting up facilities for production of silk-worm seeds or grain ages;`
  line
  line `(v) laying down the certification and silk-worm seed testing procedures for seeds sold by the`
  line `registered producers;`
  line
  line `(vi) undertaking the registration of silk-worm seed producers and dealers and controlling,`
  line `supervising the inspection process to ensure adherence to the specified quality standards and seed`
  line `certification requirements;`
  line
  line `(vii) laying down the conditions and standards for export and import of silk-worm seed and`
  line `adherence to them;`
  line
  line `(viii) programming and planning of silk-worm seed production;`
  line
  line `(ix) advising the Central Government and the State Governments on the matters aforesaid; and`
  line
  line `(x) such other matters connected and incidental to the production, supply, distribution, trade and`
  line `commerce in silk-worm seed,`
  line
  line `as may be specified by regulations made by the Committee from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_c:
  sectionId (14129)
  sectionNo 8C
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to notify kinds or varieties of silk-worm seeds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14129&sectionno=8C&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[8C. Power to notify kinds or varieties of silk-worm seeds.--(1) If the Central Government, after`
  line `consultation with the Committee, is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient to regulate the quality`
  line `of silk-worm seed of any kind or variety for the purpose of production and for commercial exploitation, it`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare such kind or variety to be a notified kind or variety`
  line `for the purposes of this Act and different kinds or varieties may be notified for different States or for`
  line `different areas thereof, and it shall be incumbent upon every producer or dealer of such silk-worm seeds`
  line `to produce or deal with such notified kinds and varieties of silk-worm seeds and in no other.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Committee, by notification,`
  line specify--
  line
  line `(a) the minimum quality standards and conditions for notified kinds or varieties of silk-worm`
  line `seed; and`
  line
  line `(b) the mark or label to indicate that such silk-worm seed conforms to the specified quality`
  line standards.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_d:
  sectionId (14130)
  sectionNo 8D
  orderNo 13
  title `Hybrid Authorisation Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14130&sectionno=8D&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[8D. Hybrid Authorisation Committee.--(1) The Committee shall constitute a Hybrid Authorisation`
  line `Committee consisting of the Secretary of the Board who shall be the Chairperson of the Hybrid`
  line `Authorisation Committee and such number of other members to assist him in the discharge of his duties`
  line `as the Committee may determine.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Hybrid Authorisation Committee to either suomotu or on the application`
  line `made to it and after due trials, testing and such other requirements, as it may deem necessary to satisfy`
  line `itself, recommend to the Committee of the kind or variety of silk-worm seed, silk-worm hybrid seeds and`
  line `races available in the market for notification by the Central Government for production and commercial`
  line exploitation.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_e:
  sectionId (14131)
  sectionNo 8E
  orderNo 14
  title `Registration Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14131&sectionno=8E&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[8E. Registration Committee.--(1) No silk-worm seed of any kind or variety shall, for the purpose of`
  line `production or for commercial exploitation, be produced, supplied, distributed, traded, sold or otherwise`
  line `disposed of by a producer or dealer unless he is registered by the Registration Committee in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall constitute the Registration Committee consisting of a Chairperson and such`
  line `number of other members not less then two to assist him in the discharge of his duties as the Committee,`
  line `may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registration Committee shall have power--`
  line
  line `(a) to register the silk-worm seed of the notified kind or variety after scrutinising claims that the`
  line `silk-worm seed conforms the kind or variety duly notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) to register the silk-worm seed producer after ensuring that the facility for seed production`
  line `meets the requirement or conditions for maintaining quality standards as notified by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) to register the silk-worm dealer after scrutinising their claim made in the application;`
  line
  line `(d) to perform such other functions as are assigned to it by the Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) Every application for registration under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and contain`
  line `such particulars including conditions and be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_f:
  sectionId (14132)
  sectionNo 8F
  orderNo 15
  title `Constitution of Seed Certification Agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14132&sectionno=8F&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[8F. Constitution of Seed Certification Agency. --The Committee may, by order, constitute one or`
  line `more Silk-worm Seed Certification Agencies or accredit the existing certification agencies according to`
  line `such criteria as may be specified by regulations to conduct inspection for registration of producers and`
  line dealers.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_g:
  sectionId (14133)
  sectionNo 8G
  orderNo 16
  title `Constitution of Central Seed Testing Laboratories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14133&sectionno=8G&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[8G. Constitution of Central Seed Testing Laboratories.--(1) The Committee may, by order,`
  line `establish the Central Seed Testing Laboratories and accredit the existing laboratories of the Board or the`
  line `State Governments having such facilities as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Seed Testing Laboratories and the accredited laboratories shall carryout such`
  line `functions as may be entrusted to it by the Committee from time to time.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee may, by order, appoint such person as it thinks fit or notify the officials or`
  line `employees of the accredited laboratories having such qualifications as may be specified by regulations to`
  line `be the Seed Analyst in the Seed Testing Laboratories and define the local limits of their jurisdiction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_h:
  sectionId (14134)
  sectionNo 8H
  orderNo 17
  title `Appointment of Seed Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14134&sectionno=8H&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[8H. Appointment of Seed Officers.--(1) The Committee may, by order, appoint such person as it`
  line `thinks fit, or notify an employee of the Board having such qualifications as may be specified by`
  line `regulations to be the Seed Officers and define the local limits of their jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Seed Officer shall be under the administrative Control of the Committee and shall be`
  line `responsible for inspecting the seeds and the facilities available with the seed producers and dealers before`
  line `or after their registration to ensure adherence to the standards and conditions laid down in this regard.`
  line
  line `(3) The Seed Officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) take samples of any silk-worm seed of any kind or variety from`
  line
  line `(i) any producer or dealer; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who is in the course of conveying such seed to a purchaser or a consignee; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a purchaser or a consignee after delivery of such seed to him;`
  line
  line `(b) exercise such other powers as may be specified by regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_i:
  sectionId (14151)
  sectionNo 8-I
  orderNo 18
  title `Export and Import of Silk-worm Seed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14151&sectionno=8-I&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[8-I. Export and Import of Silk-worm Seed. --`
  line `(1) The Committee shall advise the Central Government from time to time on the export and import`
  line `of silk-worm seed and the Central Government may, by notification, specify the terms and conditions`
  line `including exim policy for export and import of silk-worm seed.`
  line
  line `(2) All import of silk-worm seed shall conform to the quality standards specified under sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 8C.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of ensuring compliance with the conditions and quality standards for governing`
  line `such import, the Central Government may, by order, authorise officers of the level of Assistant`
  line `Commissioner to exercise the powers of inspection at the borders and ports, and such officers shall be`
  line `deemed to be the Seed Officers for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by notification, permit for research purposes, import of an`
  line `unregistered variety of silk-worm seed in such quantity and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line specified.
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, by notification, restrict the export or import of silk-worm seed of`
  line `any kind or variety if it considers that it may adversely affect the silk industry or on such other grounds,`
  line `as it may consider necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_j:
  sectionId (14152)
  sectionNo 8J
  orderNo 19
  title `Statement by silk-worm seed producers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 9(w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14152&sectionno=8J&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_8_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[8J. Statement by silk-worm seed producers.--Every registered silk-worm seed producer and dealer`
  line `shall furnish periodic statement to the Committee in such form, manner and at such intervals as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (14153)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 20
  title `Funds of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14153&sectionno=9&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall from time to time make grants to the`
  line `Board of such sums as the Central Government may consider necessary for enabling the Board to exercise`
  line `its powers and discharge its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The funds of the Board shall be kept in such bank, or, invested in such manner, as may be`
  line `prescribed and shall be expended by the Board only in the performance of its functions under this Act or`
  line `for meeting such expenses as are authorised by the Act or by rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (14154)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 21
  title `Imposition of cess on certain kinds of silk.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1953, s. 7 (w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14154&sectionno=10&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette appoint, there shall be levied and collected as a`
  line `cess for the purposes of this Act a duty of excise on all filature raw silk, and on all spun silk, reeled in the`
  line `territories to which this Act for the time being extends at such rate as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, from time to time fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The said duty of excise shall be payable by the reelers of filature raw silk or spun silk and shall be`
  line `paid by them to the Board within one month from the date of the receipt of the notice of demand from the`
  line `Board in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The said duty of excise may be recovered as if it were an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of enabling the Board to assess the amount of the duty of excise payable under`
  line `this section by the reelers of filature raw silk or spun silk,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix the period in respect of which`
  line `assessments shall be made, and`
  line
  line `(b) every reeler of filature raw silk or spun silk shall furnish to the Board within the prescribed`
  line `time a return specifying the total amount of filature raw silk or spun silk reeled during such period.`
  line
  line `(5) If any reeler of filature raw silk or spun silk fails to furnish such return within the prescribed time`
  line `or furnishes a return which the Board has reason to believe to be incorrect or defective, the Board may`
  line `assess the amount payable by such reeler in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Any reeler feeling himself aggrieved by an assessment made under this section, may, within three`
  line `months of the receipt of the notice under sub-section (2), apply to the District Judge or such other civil`
  line `judicial officer, as may be prescribed, for the cancellation or modification of the assessment; and such District Judge or judicial officer shall after giving the Board an opportunity of being heard, pass such`
  line `order as he thinks proper; and such order shall be final.`
  line
  line `^1[(7) The proceeds of the duties of excise paid to the Board shall first be credited to the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India and the Central Government may, thereafter, from time to time, pay to the Board from and`
  line `out of such proceeds such sums of money as it may think fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (14155)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 22
  title `Control by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14155&sectionno=11&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) All acts of the Board shall be subject to the control`
  line `of the Central Government which may cancel, suspend or modify as it thinks fit any action taken, or order`
  line `passed, by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The records of the Board shall be open to inspection at all reasonable times by any officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (14157)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 23
  title `Accounts of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1970, s. 4, for sub-sections (2) and (3).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14157&sectionno=12&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall keep such accounts, and in such manner and form,`
  line `as may be prescribed, respect of all moneys received and expended by it.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books,`
  line `accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded annually`
  line `to the Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(5) A copy of the accounts of the Board as so certified together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded simultaneously to the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (14158)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 24
  title `Annual report`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14158&sectionno=12A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Annual report.--The Board shall prepare for every financial year a report of its activities`
  line `and achievements during that year and submit the report to the Central Government in such form and on`
  line `or before such date as may be prescribed, and that Government shall cause a copy of the report to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (14159)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14159&sectionno=13&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under`
  line `this section may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the term of office of members of the Board, the circumstances in which and the authority by`
  line `which members may be removed and the filling of casual vacancies in the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) the procedure to be followed at meetings of the Board and at the standing committee for the`
  line `conduct of business and the number of members which shall form a quorum at any meeting;`
  line
  line `(iii) the maintenance by the Board of records of business transacted by the Board and the`
  line `submission of copies thereof to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) the holding of a minimum number of meetings every year;`
  line
  line `(v) the power of the Board, its Chairman and Standing Committee with respect to the incurring of`
  line expenditure;
  line
  line `(vi) the conditions subject to which the Board may incur expenditure outside India;`
  line
  line `(vii) the preparation of budget estimates of receipts and expenditure of the Board and the`
  line `authority by which the estimates are to be sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(viii) the maintenance of the accounts of income and expenditure of the Board^2`
  line ***;
  line
  line `^3[(viiia) the form of the annual report of the Board and the date on or before which it shall be`
  line `submitted to the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(ix) the deposit of the funds of the Board in bank and the investment of such funds;`
  line
  line `(x) the re-appropriation of estimated savings from one budget head to any other budget head;`
  line
  line `(xi) the conditions subject to which the Board may borrow funds;`
  line
  line `(xii) the conditions subject to which and the manner in which contracts may be entered into by or`
  line `on behalf of the Board;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the delegation to the Standing Committee or the ^4[Chairperson] or the ^5[Vice-Chairperson]`
  line `or members or officers of the Board of any of the powers and duties of the Board under this act;`
  line
  line `(xiv) the staff which may be employed by the Board and the pay and allowances, leave and other`
  line `conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(xv) the travelling and other allowances of members of the Board and or the Standing Committee;`
  line
  line `^6[(xva) specifying the allowances or fees of the persons associated by the Committee under subsection (2) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(xvb) matters incidental to the production, supply, distribution, trade and commerce in silk-worm`
  line `seed under clause (x) of sub-section (2) of section 8B;`
  line
  line `(xvc) manner of registration of a producer or dealer by the Registration Committee under subsection (1) and form for making application and fees to be paid under sub-section (4) of section 8E;]`
  line
  line `(xvi) the purposes for which funds of the Board may be expended;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the maintenance of the registers and other records of the Board and of its Standing`
  line Committee;
  line
  line `(xviii) the collection of any information or statistics in respect of raw silk or any product of silk;`
  line
  line `^7[(xix) the manner of grading, marketing, developing and distributing raw silk and products of silk`
  line industry;]
  line
  line `(xx) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1953, s. 8, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
  line
  line `2.The words "and the audit of such accounts"omitted by Act 21 of 1970, s. 6.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 3, for "Chairman", (w.e.f.1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Vice-Chairman" (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1.7.2007).`
  line
  line `7 Subs. by s. 10, for clause (xix) (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `8 Sub-section (3) omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (14160)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14160&sectionno=13A&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Power to make regulations. --(1) The Committee may, in consultation with the Board, and`
  line `with the previous approval of the Central Government, by notification, make regulations not inconsistent`
  line `with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, to provide for all matters for which`
  line `provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) procedure in regard to transaction of business at the meeting of the Committee under clause`
  line `(a) of sub-section (6) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(ii) laying down of various standards relating to kinds or varieties, production, testing, supply,`
  line `distribution, trade and commerce and export and import of silk-worm seed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8B;`
  line
  line `(iii) to specify the criteria for establishing Central Silk-worm Seed Certification Agencies under`
  line `section 8F, criteria and jurisdiction of Central Seed Testing Laboratories and qualifications of Seed`
  line `Analysts under sub-sections (1) and (3) of section 8G and qualifications of Seed Officers and their`
  line `other powers under sub-section (1) and clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 8H;`
  line
  line `(iv) the form, manner and intervals at which statement by producer and dealer may be furnished`
  line `under section 8J.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b:
  sectionId (14161)
  sectionNo 13B
  orderNo 27
  title `Laying of rules, regulations and notifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14161&sectionno=13B&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[13B. Laying of rules, regulations and notifications.--Every rule, regulation and notification made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `notification or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation or notification should not be made, the rule or`
  line `regulation or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the`
  line `case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation or notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (14162)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 28
  title Penalties
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14162&sectionno=14&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] If any person`
  line
  line `(a) in any return to be furnished under this Act makes any statement which is false and which he`
  line `knows to be false or does not believe to be true, or`
  line
  line `(b) obstructs any officer of the Board ^2[Committee and Registration Committee] in the exercise of`
  line `any power, conferred, or the discharge of any duty imposed on him by or under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(c) having the control or custody of any account book or other record, fails to produce such book`
  line `or record when required so to do under this Act,`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) If the person committing any offence specified in sub-section (1) is a company, every person`
  line `who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the`
  line `conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), where an offence under sub-section (1)`
  line `has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent`
  line `or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 14 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 31 of 1953. s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by the Act 42 of 2006, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the 31 of 1953, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-3-1954).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (14163)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 29
  title `Penalty for contravention of sections 8C and 8E.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 2006, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751&sectionId=14163&sectionno=14A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00002_194861_1517807318751
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Penalty for contravention of sections 8C and 8E.--If any person contravenes the provisions`
  line `of sections 8C and 8E of this Act or regulations made thereunder or any notification relating to silk-worm`
  line `seed he shall be punishable with a fine of five thousand rupees which may extend to twenty-five thousand`
  line `rupees besides suspension or cancellation of the registration to produce silk-worm seeds.]`
